                "caption": "Figure 9.Editing Abstractions with a Vision-Language Model.The VLM agent receives as input the proxy’s JSON file—where each primitive is described by its scale, rotation, translation, and shape exponent parameters—a text editing instruction, the rendering of the original shape, and multi-view renderings of the proxy. It then produces an updated JSON file, which is used to generate new multi-view renderings of the edited proxy. This process repeats iteratively, with the outputs from the previous step fed back to the VLM agent, until the edit is confirmed or the maximum number of iterations is reached.",
